President Donald Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key positions in his administration. The nominations include James N. Stewart for Assistant Secretary of Defense (Manpower and Reserve Affairs), John F. Ring for Member of the National Labor Relations Board, Johnathan Miller for Assistant Administrator (Bureau for Africa) of the United States Agency for International Development, Thomas E. Ayres for General Counsel of the Department of the Air Force, Michael Stoker for Director of the Federal Mediation and Conciliation Service, Kenneth Steven Barbic for Assistant Secretary of Agriculture (Congressional Affairs), Jackie Wolcott for Representative of the United States of America on the Board of Governors of the International Atomic Energy Agency, Francis R. Fannon for Assistant Secretary of State (Energy Resources).